Scatologists identified the panda droppings in the region's Qinling mountains where it lived 30 years ago, while locals have reported sighting animals resembling the bear, Xinhua news agency reported.
Giant pandas will not eat the bamboo after it blooms and it takes 10 years for a new supply to grow.
Currently more than 1,500 giant pandas live wild in China, according to a survey by the State Forestry Administration.
The third national survey on giant pandas, which began in 2000 and ended last year, shows that pandas live in mountain areas of 20 towns of eight counties along the east-west Qinling Mountain inShaanxi Province.
